(firstQuint)Evaluation of Hand Assessments in Children With Severe Hand Burns.

 Children will be given a battery of tests to determine the validity of these measures for children with severe hand burns.

 The tests include: - Pinch and grip strength; - Stereognosis; - Speed of manipulation using the Nine Hole Peg Test, Box & Blocks Test, and the Moberg Pickup Test; - Measurement of Range of Motion of the wrist and fingers.

